<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="390" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1267,1584]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1267,1293]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Distribution:</emphasis>
Known from the Amazonian foothills at the northeastern Andes of 
<collectingCountry box="[1063,1117,1268,1294]" name="Peru" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Peru</collectingCountry>
, eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1215,1310,1267,1293]" name="Ecuador" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, the mountain range of 
<collectingRegion box="[307,391,1303,1329]" country="Venezuela" name="Merida" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Mérida</collectingRegion>
, the Amazonia in 
<collectingCountry box="[602,720,1303,1329]" name="Venezuela" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, and in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[965,1075,1303,1329]" name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Pires, T." box="[1092,1290,1303,1332]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 706" refId="ref15408" refString="Avila-Pires, T. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivas, G. A. &amp; Molina, C. R. &amp; Ugueto, G. N. &amp; Barros, T. R. &amp; Barrio-Amoros C. L. &amp; Kok P. J. R." pageId="13" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref18566" refString="Rivas, G. A., Molina, C. R., Ugueto, G. N., Barros, T. R., Barrio-Amoros C. L. &amp; Kok P. J. R. (2012) Reptiles of Venezuela: an updated and commented checklist. Zootaxa, 3211 (1), 1 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3211.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Rivas 
<emphasis box="[1378,1437,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[265,378,1339,1365]" name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, this species is distributed in the eastern slope of the Cordillera Oriental and the Amazonian region (
<figureCitation box="[238,329,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps for the cis-Andean microteiid lizards in Colombia (Alopoglossidae + Gymnophthalmidae). Circles are examined specimens, while squares are records from literature (see Supplementary Files for specific references). Red arrows indicate new records for Colombia. Black arrows show a zoom in to regions where several records overlap. The light green shadow indicates the Orinoco River basin, and the dark green the Amazon River basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5681929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5681929/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1267,1584]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,388,1411,1437]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Similar species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[397,638,1411,1437]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">
<emphasis box="[397,638,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Loxopholis parietalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other cis-Andean congenerics by the presence of a large fourth pair of chin-shields (reduced in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ayala &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[587,723,1447,1473]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hexalepis">
<emphasis box="[587,723,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. hexalepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[778,960,1448,1473]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis box="[778,960,1448,1473]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); keeled ventral scales (smooth or weakly keeled in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esqueda" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[263,414,1484,1509]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caparensis">
<emphasis box="[263,414,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. caparensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, smooth in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ayala &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[551,688,1483,1509]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hexalepis">
<emphasis box="[551,688,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. hexalepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); rhomboid dorsals (hexagonal to rectangular with straight lateral margins in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[278,443,1519,1545]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[278,443,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and a large frenocular scale (small frenocular scale in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[1080,1244,1519,1545]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[1080,1244,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). For a more detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Pires, T." box="[395,608,1555,1584]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 706" refId="ref15408" refString="Avila-Pires, T. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires (1995)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
